accd -- ACC dedicated server reimplementation (work in progress)

Clean-room reimplementation of the Assetto Corsa Competizione
dedicated server, built so an unmodified ACC game client can connect
and play a private multiplayer session without any traffic to Kunos's
backend.  See ../notebook-b/NOTEBOOK_B.md for the protocol
specification this code is working towards.

STATUS
    Phase 1.  TCP framing layer + handshake parser + handshake response
    builder + module-level dispatch skeleton for every TCP and UDP
    message id known to the catalog.  All non-handshake cases are
    stubs that log the msg id and length but do not yet mutate state.

BUILD
    make

    Tested on Linux (aarch64, Debian sid, gcc 15) with -Wall -Wextra
    -Wpedantic.  Intended to also build on OpenBSD without changes:
    iconv is in libc on both platforms, the Makefile uses no GNU-isms,
    and the source pledges "stdio inet" on OpenBSD after the ports
    are bound.

RUN
    The server expects a cfg/ directory containing configuration.json
    and (optionally) settings.json + event.json, all UTF-16 LE per
    the Kunos server layout.  Pass the cfg directory as the first
    argument:

        ./accd ../acc-server/server/cfg

    or run it from the stock server's directory:

        cd /path/to/acc-server/server
        /path/to/accd/accd

    It prints the parsed config, binds the configured ports, runs a
    poll loop with a periodic tick, and logs handshake activity until
    interrupted (Ctrl-C).

SMOKE TESTS
    Reject path:
        printf '\x03\x00\x09\x99\x00' | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 $tcpPort
    expects a 9-byte rejection response with reason byte = 1
    (REJECT_VERSION).

    Accept path (empty server password):
        printf '\x04\x00\x09\x00\x01\x00' | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 $tcpPort
    expects a ~41-byte 0x0b response with car id 0 and the welcome
    trailer skeleton.

MODULES
    main.c       poll loop, signal handling, server lifecycle
    config.c/h   UTF-16 LE JSON config reader (flat fields only)
    state.c/h    per-connection and global server state
    msg.h        all 31+22 message id constants and enums
    io.c/h       byte buffer and TCP framing (u16 + 0xFFFF escape)
    prim.c/h    little-endian primitive readers/writers, Format-A
                 and Format-B wide-string codecs
    net.c/h      tcp_listen / udp_bind helpers
    log.c/h      timestamped stderr logger with hexdump
    handshake.c/h  parse 0x09 ACP_REQUEST_CONNECTION, build 0x0b
                 response (accept or reject)
    dispatch.c/h  TCP framed-message dispatch + UDP datagram dispatch
                 with all 21 TCP and 7 UDP cases stubbed out
    chat.c/h     admin chat command parser skeleton
    tick.c/h     periodic tick stub for future broadcasters
    lan.c/h      UDP 8999 LAN discovery handler

STYLE
    Portable C99.  libc + iconv only.  KNF-ish with tab indentation.
    sigaction(2) not signal(3), pledge(2) on OpenBSD.  No dynamic
    allocation in the hot paths beyond what the byte buffer needs.
